subparagraph.content:
in co-operation with the proper authorities, any person to or from any
                    hospital or clinic to or from any other place, and administer care and attention
                    to any person so conveyed;

that closes any premises in relation to which a person has been convicted
                    of an offence under this Ordinance in accordance with the regulation made under
                        section 25(1)(hb)(ii);

that prohibits any premises to be used for a particular purpose in
                    accordance with the regulation made under section
                    25(1)(hb)(iv);

paragraph.content:
conferring on a subordinate officer or a member of other ranks the rights
                    of appeal against a finding or punishment set out in that Schedule;
                    and

nothing in this Part shall be construed to preclude the summary dismissal of
                any member in accordance with Public Service (Administration) Order and government
                regulations;

section.def:
acquire
                (取得) means acquire by purchase or by any other
            lawful means;

corporation
                (法團) means the corporation sole constituted under
                section 19(1);

function
                (職能) includes a power, an authority and a
            duty;

Fund
                (基金) means the Fire Services Department Welfare
            Fund continued by section 19A;

paragraph.content:
all fees paid for the services of members detailed by the Director to perform
                special services under section 23 and for the use of equipment referred
                to in that section;

the registration and de-registration of registered fire engineers;
                        (Added 1 of 2017 s.
                    5)

subparagraph.content:
that requires a person to remove any article or thing that obstructs or
                        may obstruct, or locks or may lock the means of escape in any
                        premises;

paragraph.content:
by carelessness or neglect in the performance of his duty contributes
                        to the occurrence of any loss, damage or injury to any person or
                        property;

section.def:
accused (被控人)
                    means a subordinate officer or a member of other ranks charged with an offence
                    against discipline;

defence representative (辯護代表) means a person specified in rule
                        5(1)(a) or (b) of this Part who represents an accused at a
                    hearing;

paragraph.content:
if in the Director’s opinion the evidence does not show that any
                            offence against discipline has been committed, dismiss the
                            charge;

a copy of the written record of proceedings made in respect of the
                            case under rule 9(1) of this Part which has been certified by the
                            Director to be a true copy of the original;

subparagraph.content:
order either a further investigation by the Director, or a fresh
                            investigation in a manner and by a person or persons that the Chief
                            Executive thinks fit;

